6 HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES
7 132ND LEGISLATURE
8 FIRST SPECIAL SESSION
9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 552, L.D. 866, “An Act to Reduce
10 Posting of Hunting Lands by Providing Free Antlerless Deer Permits to Certain
11 Landowners Who Keep Their Lands Open to Hunting”
12 Amend the bill by striking out the title and substituting the following:
13 'Resolve, Directing the Department of Inland Fisheries and Wildlife to Implement a
14 Landowner Antlerless Deer Permit Gift Program'
15 Amend the bill by striking out everything after the title and inserting the following:
16 'Sec. 1. Program established. Resolved: That the Department of Inland Fisheries
17 and Wildlife shall establish and implement a landowner antlerless deer permit gift program,
18 referred to in this resolve as "the program," under which a person may purchase an
19 antlerless deer permit for a landowner for $12 as a gesture of appreciation for a landowner
20 that allows hunting on the landowner's land.
21 Sec. 2. Report. Resolved: That, no later than January 1, 2027, the Department of
22 Inland Fisheries and Wildlife shall submit a report to the joint standing committee of the
23 Legislature having jurisdiction over inland fisheries and wildlife matters that includes an
24 overview of the program and any suggested recommendations for legislative changes. The
25 report must also include a description of the ways the department has engaged with and
26 shown appreciation to landowners that allow hunting on those landowners' properties and
27 the outreach conducted by the department to encourage hunters to show appreciation to
28 landowners that allow hunting on those landowners' properties. The committee may report
29 out a bill related to the report to the 133rd Legislature in 2027.'
30 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
31 number to read consecutively.
32 SUMMARY
3333 This amendment replaces the bill with a resolve. The amendment directs the
3344 Department of Inland Fisheries and Wildlife to establish and implement a landowner
